470	  // refresh_tokens.device_id has ON DELETE RESTRICT in MySQL — simply
471	  // soft-revoking (setting revokedAt) leaves the rows in place and the
472	  // subsequent device.delete() would fail with a FK constraint violation.
473	  // Removing a device implies the user no longer authorizes any session
474	  // bound to it, so deleting the refresh tokens (rather than just marking
